cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI

This paper discusses the use of citation analysis in academia, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on databases and tools for citation searching suggests that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category. The use of citation analysis for hiring, promotion, and funding decisions suggests relevance to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as well. The discussion of quality and language of citations may be relevant to cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CR (Computers and Society). Finally, the examination of over 10,000 citing documents suggests relevance to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
